Error ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- test.js:61:3

Cannot cast `rwB` to `RWA` because in property `p`: `B` [1] is not exactly the same as `A` [2]. [incompatible-type]

The above-mentioned two types must be the same because property `p` is invariantly typed. To fix the error,
- Either make `RWB` [3] and `RWA` [4] exactly the same
- Or make property `p` in `RWA` [5] readonly. See
https://flow.org/en/docs/faq/#why-cant-i-pass-a-string-to-a-function-that-takes-a-string-number.

   test.js:61:3
   61|   rwB as RWA; // error
         ^^^

